# i3-blocks

This directory is called etc because the configuration file for i3blocks is located in /etc 
directory. Firstly you need to download i3blocks to your conputer. the easiest way is 
with terminal ( You can check master ReadMe file). After installation you have to edit 
your i3blocks.conf file as root. If there is no i3blocks.conf file located in your /etc 
directory just download mine and copy it into /etc directory. After logging out/it you 
should be able to see  time/volume/internet on your i3Bar. You can easily change 
what you and don't want to see on your i3bar just by editing i3blocks.conf file (don't 
forget to log out/in for after changes to take effect). 
